caption: Me and my wife had dinner for our 30th wedding anniversary. A friend recommend it and we where not disappointed at all. The food is amazing and a great atmosphere. We would give it more stars if we could. Our waiter Cam was great as well. Thanks to Amelias for a wonderful dinner.
Food was phenomenal.  Service was great.  Will be visiting again, soon!
Great steak!

This is one of the best restaurants we have ever been to. Five stars for everything from being seated to dessert. We were just passing through Gainesville, but we are going to need to make a trip back to dine at this exquisite restaurant again.
Nothing seems fresh, likely microwave food a chef mic (microwave) situation. They're only popular due to lacation. Don't waste your money.

This place is absolutely amazing. The food has always been spot on, and the service is great! It's my favorite place to go for a special occasion. The surf & turf special is amazing, as are many of the pastas. We also get the cheesecake duo every time, because it's amazing no matter what the flavors are. There is some outdoor seating, which is great for right now. Overall it's probably best to make a reservation so you know they won't be full.
Hands down our favorite restaurant in Gainesville.   Impeccable service and the food is outstanding EVERY time!

I really enjoyed the veil parm and the wine/ beer selection. It's a very nice place to go for special occasions just make sure to reserve ahead of time, I did not know this before hand and showed after they opened. Instead of turning us away one host was generous enough to give me and my gf a spot. This made our early valentine's date fantastic. Thank you so much Lupin.
Wonderful atmosphere, great service...The chicken caprese was absolutely AMAZING!
Great food and excellent curbside service!  Lucky to have a restaurant of this quality in Gainesville!
Best restaurant in town, hands down. Chef Andy and his staff always provide an amazing experience. Can’t recommend this place highly enough.

If you've not been to Amelia's, you are missing out on the BEST Italian food in Gainesville. Chef Andy does a phenomenal job with the menu and is an exceptional cook. The entire staff at Amelia's will take very good care of you, should you decide to dine there, and believe me, you should dine there.
This is the very best restaurant in North Florida.
It was not what we thought. We thought it was a simple italian restaurant. We were very wrong. It's very upscale and expensive.The place smelled amazing. Parking was difficult.

This restaurant is fabulous! The food is delicious and authentic and the service impecable!! Thank you Drew for your recommendatioms and the attentive service!  We cannot wait to return!!  Alisa , Craig and Savannah at ZENISON
Great service and cool atmosphere. Calamari was really good as was the dessert. The pasta dish I got was ok but would try a different one next time.
First time here and the food bread and drink was so tasty. We had a great date here.
I had chicken parmesan with side of asparagus, everything was delicious. Prices were reasonable! Atmosphere was nice.

Food was amazing. First time there and I was very impressed. Great place for a date night, or just a nice night out for dinner. Chef Andy came over and introduced himself as the owner. He runs a great business from what i saw, and I wish many years of success to this place. I would advise anyone who plans on going there, you get what you pay for. And you pay for amazing food and great service. Support local businesses!
Best restaurant in Gainesville! Delicious food, great service and relaxing atmosphere.
Very welcoming atmosphere, competent and friendly staff. And best of all AMAZING FOOD!!

Delicious food and great service. My wife and I came a few days after our wedding recently to celebrate just the 2 of us and they presented us with champagne. The food was fresh, and drinks were delicious. Definitely recommend.
Absolutely phenomenal! We went here for a family dinner and everything was amazing! Get the chef specials! The chef even comes to personally check if your liked your meal! Definitely coming back!
Love the food  Great quiet place to go
The manicotti is excellent!  The grouper dishes are also wonderful.   Consistently great service.

This restaurant is truly worthy of a five star rating. The most tender Veal Frances that could be cut with a fork. My friend ordered chicken Parm which was equally as tender. Another guest enjoyed eggplant Parm who  said was spectacular and our final guest ordered a salmon dish which was truly delectable. Wonderful service in a relaxed atmosphere and even the hot bread was amazing. Don’t miss this place when you are in Gainesville
Absolutely the best Italian restaurant and the almond custard is like nothing else! Excellent service and friendly atmosphere.

Perfectly executed calamari in marinara. Huge chunks of tender squid in every bite. My wife chicken alfredo tortellini was creamy, delicious and perfectly seasoned. A delightful random find this weekend with plenty of socially distant outside seating.
amazing food! the chef is super kind and even came to speak to us. loved it and will be back!

My boyfriend and I came on our anniversary and our server, Meghan, was incredible! Top notch service and she was so incredibly helpful. The food was amazing, everyone should try the pesto linguini!!! We will definitely be coming back!

Went two weekends ago and sat outside. It was perfect. Food was delicious! From appetizer to dessert. Fresh bread also! Amanda, our server, was awesome. Very personable and on top of things!! Definitely be back!!
Food and service is great but the fast paced jazz music kills the ambiance

I am in town for the weekend and I picked Amelia's because it smelled really good as I was walking by and I liked the outdoor patio setting. I was immediately seated and the service was impeccable and the people were very friendly and the chef came out several times and stopped to have a conversation. On top of that the food was absolutely amazing. The bread is fresh and I had the grouper and it was like nothing I'd ever had before. The sauce was amazing and the grouper was the biggest thickest piece of fish I've ever seen. The side of pasta seemed like a second thought as it had a different sauce on it so I didn't bother with that. Probably would have eaten it if it was in the same sauce as the grouper was. The locals that were next to me that I had a conversation with had all wonderful things to say about them as well and the dessert which I never made it to because I ate so much of the fresh bread. I would highly recommend that everyone visits this place at least once a visit.

Omg all the reviews are correct. This place was amazing! Must do! I loved the food! Was in town for the weekend. From Orlando. And I wish I could come back more often. I'm not a sea food person. But my mom who got the steamed clams and the calamari were the best she has had in a long time.
Great food.
Great food. I had the tortellini alfredo it was excellent

Excellent food.  Great portions.  A properly run restaurant with a top notch chef trained at a premier culinary school. I happen to go to the same school as he did and it shows in his creations. Everything was excellent.

AMAZING staff and incredible food! Unfortunately I did not go inside due to COVID (we sat outside) but our waitress Meghan was outstanding and so friendly. The chef/owner also came out on three separate occasions to make sure everything was up to par (which it was!). I would highly recommend dining here!
Chicken parm amazing.  Eggplant parm "best ever eaten" Amanda great service! We'll be back for more!

I simply MUST rave here about many suggestions to eat at Amelia's Fine Italian Cuisine - Gainesville! Holy holy HOLY mackerel that was THE BEST ITALIAN I HAVE EVER HAD!  The spinach dip? I wanted to lick the plate. It’s honestly THAT good.  My husband had surf n turf and he wanted to make love to the plate. (Sorry, tmi, but an accurate description!)  I had tortellini with pesto and WHOAAAAAAA, I am in complete heaven!  I was so stuffed when we were done eating, I couldn’t even fathom taking anything with me because I want to lay in bed in my food coma!!  HANDS DOWN, Andy, the chef/owner was kind and caring throughout our meal. Meaghan our server? She was immaculate in her service.  I cannot recommend such a phenomenally owned and operated establishment!! Thank you Andy and Meaghan!
Fine dining at its peak. Everything was perfect from the decor to drinks to food. Highly recommend the surf n turf. Will be back for next date night.
Great food, awesome service,  nice outdoor dining area

Excellent upscale Italian cuisine in the historic downtown area. Amelia's makes delicious food that has a wonderful combination of flavors, elevating your traditional Italian dishes. This is not the place where you're going to get a mountain of so-so pasta on a paper table cloth. They're well set up for a group, I came here with a group from UF. The ambiance is nice without being too loud to allow for conversation. Excellent service.

I went here for my anniversary. It is very classy and the staff is very nice. The chef/owner came out with a saxophone to play happy birthday for this kids birthday and it was very sweet! I love the atmosphere!

Literally the best service we have ever had hands down. The food was amazing, with a lot of local ingredients, but the service was absolutely the best. Our server Drew was very attentive and knowledgeable about the restaurant and menu, and the owner and chef Andy visited all tables to check on food, etc. He also bussed tables, called a guest who had left his credit card, played the saxophone for a guest's birthday, and brought over a tray of local mushrooms to show my husband and myself what types were in the dish we had ordered. He clearly cares a great deal for his restaurant, the food quality, and guest happiness. I want to go here 10000 times more. SO GOOD!

I reserved a table here twice now, and have not been disappointed. The first time we went was on a date, and it needed to be perfect for my wife and I. The environment was perfect, the chef/owner is amazing. We both thought it was the best fettuccini Alfredo we have ever had. The second time we went recently was for a birthday. The owner/chef came out and PLAYED A SAXAPHONE HAPPY BIRTHDAY. Was absolutely thrilled. We will never go to the gainesville olive garden ever again, will only go here. Cannot recommend enough. The only consideration is to go early when they open. people bring babies in and the crying tends to ruin a good date.
Really good Italian food. Chef Andy is great.
I really like the vibe at this place!
Had the grouper, awesome, but I still like the surf and turf the best

Food was awesome. Best Italian food I have had. Their ravioli was cooked perfectly and was so tasty. The chef who is also the owner, Andy checked in on us a couple of times. The service was great. Our server India was awesome and she made sure she checked on our parking spot (which is a little tricky) to ensure we dont get a ticket. Definitely worth a visit

One of the best served authentic Italian foods The waiters were very friendly and provided great service.. the way they accommodate your needs in terms of food restrictions and palette preference is awesome.  The head chef meets you personally to make sure your order has met your expectations. I dont live around the Gainesville area. If I did , I would be at Amelia's for every special dinner night:-)
Great food and service! The chef was very nice and came to check on us several times.
They have good Italian food at good prices. And lunch specials! Dang. Count me in.

Great food, and fantastic service.  Went to a Rehearsal Dinner with a party of 25.  Seated comfortably in a pleasantly isolated back room, served quickly by very pleasant and attentive staff.  I was especially pleased with how well they catered to our two small children in an otherwise adult set of customers (best chicken fingers I've ever tasted!).
Awesome dining  experience.   My mom and had a great time!
Best fish I've ever had, great and authentic Italian. Server was amazing, cozy setting and just delicious.

From greeting to seating to servers, it was outstanding. Great half off wine by the bottle night. Bread and evoo right out. Suggestion by server were fantastic. Owner/chef plays saxophone for happy birthday to guests, such fun. Enjoyed veal and salmon at our table with Cesar salad to start and side of house pasta and red sauce. Chef works the crowd with personal interactions. Dessert of pistachio and sambuco. What a wonderful dining experience!
Nice Italian restaurant tucked away behind a shopping center. They do a good lunch service since the courthouse is 1 block away.
Great food great service and great atmosphere.
Fantastic as usual.
We were in town over the holidays and came here for Christmas dinner. The waitstaff was great, as was the food.
Great vibe
Food is awesome!  Service impeccable!
Always great.
Great food, but service was a bit slow and not properly shown the drinks and specials.
Very good atmosphere!! I felt  treated special even with a busy hour!! Thanks!!
Absolutely amazing.  Whenever I'm in Gainesville I always make sure I go. Food is to die for,  great atmosphere and phenomenal service.
Great food
Very cozy great atmosphere wonderful staff and the cook and owner comes out and chatts with the people. Food was wonderful
a bit salty/ marina served with side pasta is disappointing. calamari is delicious
Good food and very accomodating of dietary restrictions.
Try the appetizers too.😋

I don’t think I could ever justify spending any amount of money at Olive Garden for a family of 3 again, especially when for only a tiny bit more, I can come here and have 1) better, actually freshly made food, 2) much friendlier and more informative wait staff, 3) an interaction with the head chef, 4) a very classy atmosphere, and 5) the chance to support a local business. Absolutely one of the best dining experiences I’ve ever had. If you want dessert recommendations: get the almond custard, it’s to die for. It comes with these dark, slightly sour cherries and cherry sauce on top, and it’s served in an edible bowl. I also ordered the tortellini alfredo, and it was amazing; soft and fresh pasta plus rich cheese, none of that frozen, rubbery garbage. If I could give this place more than five stars I would.
Excellent food and service, if a little pricey

I've tried their Tortellini Pesto and Chicken Parmigiana. The Tortellini Pesto is very creamy and heavy, so if you're having this for lunch, you're going to want to take a nap afterwards. The Chicken Parmigiana is just your standard chicken parm, nothing special. They're good dishes, however if you're expecting Italian food like what you find in the northeast, this is not the place to go.
Slow. Everything tastes like it’s out of a freezer Box.
Great atmosphere ,food and service
Excellent food
Food FOOD  FOOD❣ABSOLUTELY DELICIOUS.
NEVER  disappoints! Most tasty and pleasantly crafted meals. Chef Andy and staff make dining here an absolute delight!
Very nice clean place and the food is great and the location is very quaint in downtown Gville.
Amelia's lunch deal is one of the best in town. Great food, service, prices, portions are just right and warm bread too

The most rich  flavorful Chicken Marsala I have ever had.  The chef Andy uses sherry so the marsala is not too heavy and not too sweet.  The perfect marsala!! Excellent table service by Amanda.   Thank you for a fabulous meal!!!

They even brought out three different fresh artisanal breads that were great. House salad was good, the lettuce could be cut into smaller pieces, and there could be more vegetables. It only had one slice of cucumber, carrot, and mushroom- so it was a bit sad. The owner and executive chef did come out twice and greet himself and ask how we were doing, that was very kind of him and the service in general was amazing.
Good classics Italian restaurant
The surf and turf is amazing!

My husband and I love this place.  We have been coming here for years and it's still our favorite place.  Chef Andy is great and so is the staff.  My personal faves are Eggplant Parm and Salmon Andaluccia, but really anything I ever ordered here has been divine!
Incredibly good food and even better service!
Very good place, dinner was amazing. The Chef is also the owner!

I had a business trip out to Gainesville and heard about Amelia’s. Well worth the side trip. The food is delicious and timed the right way - no rush at all. I had fried calamari that certainly were fresh. The scallopini was done just right. Good wine selection including a few Chianti but unfortunately no Barolo. The final espresso was divine. The diner took the appropriate two hours so we got things done over a wonderful dinner. Even the chef roamed around to see if things were right. Go here for a truly great meal.
Italian food and the atmosphere here is great. it's so tasty. i had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here.

I've not been to Amelia's for dinner yet but I do know it's a perfect lunch spot in Gainesville! The food is delish and so reasonably priced. Great selection of soup and salad combinations. Also got the eggplant parmesan... (had to order another one to go!) And the desserts that are handcrafted right there. Yes, please... more to take home to share!
Nice atmosphere and delicious latin food.
Excellent Food Upscale Yumy
The food was excellent and the customer service was very good. All of the servers were very efficient with the drinks and orders. I would recommend Amelia's. The chicken posa posa was very good.
Love it!  Food and service are excellent.

Amelia's has been a "default" restaurant when I'm in town for Florida Gator football games for many years. They take reservations which are easy to make. Their wine list is excellent as well as the many Italian entrees featured on the menu. We are always pleased when we walk out of the restaurant at the end of our meal. You can't go wrong by coming here.

Great food and staff.  Andy the chef/owner always makes his way around to greet every table.  He and his staff have never disappointed.  My favorite is the surf and turf, and my wife loves the salmon.  Awesome place for special occasions.  Andy even plays the Saxaphone table side for guests celebrating birthdays.
Excellent food, great service

I visited Amelia’s Italian Cuisine in Gainesville and it was great! I was totally craving chicken carbonara which wasn’t on the menu and they made it just for me! My family enjoyed their meals as well and my mother in law ordered the grouper and it was a big cut and it was delicious. I had a cappuccino for dessert and my father in law enjoyed the Spumoni. The executive chef and owner Andy was checking on his guests and was engaged. He was very personable and we enjoyed his interaction with us. I recommend Amelia’s when you’re in Gainesville and we will definitely be back!

Literally everything deserves a 5 Star. The food, the service, the wait time (or lack thereof).... couldn’t recommend this place more. The chef/owner came by and checked on us, even played with my 9 month old a little (usually people hate kids but this certainly was not the case). Everyone in my family ordered something different and we all agreed each meal was the best of its kind. Excited to go back!

The food here is amazing. The lasagna I had was phenomenal, the caprese was really good, and my girlfriend's shrimp pasta dish looked tasty but I'm allergic so i can only guess. The restaurant has a very warm intimate atmosphere. Fantastic date night restaurant.
Great lunch specials and food is very well prepared nice size portion and delicious, comes out quickly.
A fine Italian dining experience. Friendly service and tasty food in downtown Gainesville with good options for vegetarians.
Great food! Service has been good everytime I visit. Steak topped with Shrimp special is delicious.

Amelia's is one of the best Italian restaurants we've eaten at. Thanks to tripadvisor reviewers for this wonderful discovery! Everything about our dinner was perfect. The food was delicious, the atmosphere was lovely, and service was friendly and well paced. We chose an appetizer for 2 that included stuffed mushrooms, eggplant, and mussels. The salads were fresh and beautifully presented. It was hard to decide on our dinner entrees because of so many excellent choices, but we both decided on the grouper with lemon sauce, capers, and Greek olives - outstanding! The portion was very large, and the entree came with a side dish of ziti in marinara sauce - also excellent. If we are ever back in Gainesville, we will definitely return to Amelia's.
Nice Italian dinner

One of the best, if not the best, restaurants I've been to in Gainesville. Both the food and service were top notch. I ordered one of the veal dishes and it was easily the best veal I have ever tasted. I could not get enough. Our server informed us that the chef goes out to the farm and selects the calves himself. The restaurant paid great attention to detail and helped to make a wonderful night. It is on the pricer side, but you will not be disappointed by the quality you will receive.
Great Italian restaurant with reasonably priced options. I had the pasta with mushrooms dish from the specials menu and added a little protien, outstanding!

Exceptional experience. Everything was impeccable and I couldn't have chosen a better destination for my birthday dinner. The kitchen accommodated our table's allergy.  Executive chef and owner Andy stopped by our table multiple times to make sure our party of 4 was enjoying our dinner, and he played a musical rendition of "Happy Birthday"  on the sax. My only regret is not trying Amelia's sooner.
Best Pesto sauce I've ever had... Wow!!!
Good service but food was very disappointing, especially for the reasonably high price charged. Interesting sounding dishes but very bland and unimpressive
Ok, better choices downtown area. Way over priced for noodles and sauce.
Best cannoli filling I've eaten, and I've eaten many.

Amelia’s Restaurant is a must if you are in Gainesville and love Italian food. We make it a point to eat here whenever we are in town. The servers are wonderful and the food is amazing. The owner/chef is very friendly too. Highly recommend this restaurant.
A great place for a quick lunch or romantic dinner.
Food was outstanding.  Service was good. Cozy atmosphere.

Drew was our server and he was great. We got two entrees from the Special and they were delicious (though a bit salty to us). The chef came out to say hello at the end of our meal - it was pleasant. Will definitely come back again!

Enjoyed an amazing time with family here Christmas night. The service was wonderful, the food had to have been the best I've ever had. I ordered the steak and shrimp with red potatoes covered in parmesan cream sauce and it was phenomenal. I am pregnant so had to order my steak cooked a little more than I typically would, and to my surprise, it was still so tender I could cut it with a spoon. My fiance actually proposed to me here and it was perfect. The owner/chef made rounds to check on each and every guest. The atmosphere is romantic and relaxing. I definitely recommend this restaurant for a nice evening out with your significant other. I can't wait to go again.
Friendly service, amazing food.
Place is nice and staff very friendly. Food is good. Price is a bit high (we were 3 and bill without tip was $100) Overall very good
Good
Nice place, good attention. Food was good but too salty.

An unexpected surprise to find this  exceptional restaurant. The food is top notch (and a fair price), the waitstaff highly attentive, and the owner/head chef is a delightful man who tends well to his customers. Can’t recommend a place more highly than this.
Very nice Italian fine food and wine!!!
Lunch is just as delicious as dinner at an affordable price. With hot bread, white table clothes and smiling service.
The food is amazing. Friendly staff. A simple soup, dinner salad, and bread is worth a 30 minute wait, really. So good. A favorite dinner spot. I'll keep coming back whenever in Gainesville.
Great place. The food was outstanding and the service was excellent. Definitely a place to visit if you're in the area.
Food and services was amazing.

Gainesville does not have that many quality Italian restaurants which is a shame, but Amelias almost always delivers.  The menu is large and varied, with ample choices from chicken parmesan to veal milanese to  grouper.  Service is usually very good.  Tuesday night, wine is half price.  There are many other reviews, but you really can't go wrong here.
Food was amazing.  Service a little off.  Parking not the easiest.

(Translated by Google) This was my fifth time at Amelia's. Small restaurant, quiet and pleasant. This time I took my bottle of wine, which was well accepted by the chef and owner of the place. The special of the day was fantastic grouper. I'll come back again.  (Original) Esta foi minha quinta vez no Amelia’s. Restaurante pequeno, silencioso e agradável. Desta vez levei minha garrafa de vinho, o que foi bem aceito pelo chef e dono do local. O especial do dia era fantástica garoupa ao forno. Retornarei outra vez.
It's been many years since I ate there, but back then it was fabulous!
Exceptional food and service
Great place with delicious food

Great lunch, great service, good service! Lunches under $10! Nice atmosphere! Lunch is guaranteed in under 15 minutes. For such good food and great atmosphere I think the 15 minute guarantee is almost impossible to keep! :-)
Wonderful food selection.
Great food

Wonderful Bolognese, fish portion was huge.  Wait staff was attentive.  The Chef uses tomato's for his sauce from a specialty tomato broker instead of the normal restaurant supply company and you can tell.

I cannot express how luxurious this place is for an affordable price! Amelia’s was my boyfriend and I’s first date spot 2 years ago and will forever be our favorite spot in Gainesville. The surf and turf special is absolutely incredible, I seriously am constantly thinking about it. I’ve tried to recreate their made-to-order blue cheese/garlic sauce many times, but I will never be able to master it the way they do. I’m salovating just thinking about it! The customer service is always impeccable and the bread selection they provide before your meal is always baked to perfection. Chef Andy also plays “happy birthday” on saxophone for customers and it is always incredibly fun for the whole restaurant to enjoy. Truly an unmatched Italian Restaurant experience! After many visits I can honestly say that is impossible to be disappointed at this place.
Absolutely amazing. The food was beyond delicious, the service was friendly, and we even met the executive chief. It was perfect for our special occasion and will definitely be visiting again!
Service I was wonderful,  atmosphere very nice. I had the eggplant parmesan, it was good, though I couldn't find enough cheese.  I like cheese between the layers,  this had cheese only on top.
Great food
The owner and staff were amazing. The lobster pasta is to die for. The owner/chef Andy came out to make sure ALL of his guest were happy. Now that's what I call service.
Great food, great service. Will be going back soon. A must visit gem...
I had the lobster ravioli, which melted in my mouth. My daughter had the tortellini Alfredo and it was even better than mine. I wish I were staying longer to go back and enjoy it again.
Always a fantastic meal and top notch service!
Fabulous

Great food, Great service!  Highly recommend.The Brushetta appetizer is very flavorful and  fresh. The  Chicken Parmagen ,Veal  Francesse and Mushroom Pasta dish were  was fantastic.  We had the cheesecake special ( bannana foster and blueberry duo)  and the coffee ice cream were really good. Chef Andy came by to check on us. A great place for dinner. We will be back!
Loved how the owner received us and sat us down on our table, really goes out to show they care about providing the best service. Food was delicious. It is a great place for special events.

We had a long very time with a party of 12 in the Jazz Room at Amelia’s. Very good food. A number of us had one of the four preparations of grouper ($27-$28).  The lobster ravioli special was good. Desserts included spumoni, which many of have not seen in Italian restaurants.  Walter was helpful and spirited. The chef came out to play saxophone for a birthday!  We were left to enjoy our time. I recommend Amelia’s for its food, service and atmosphere.
Always have a GREAT meal here, was disappointed with the parking issue but it es not the restaurants fault.
awesome good. i tried the new York strips and my wife tried tortellini Alfredo. delicious. and drew, our server did a great job, and knows pretty good the city and other places to check in.
Superb service & great flavor!! I do recommend and I will try to come back when I visit town.

Beautiful outside area for evenings in a quiet pedestrian zone. Everything else was unfortunately just "OK". One glass had lipstick stains from the former guests but was quickly replaced. Napkins were quickly brought on request. Food was ok. Service was quick and friendly. Very good complementary bread. This should have been a 4-star review, but I was negativity surprised when I saw that a 20% gratitude was automatically added to our check (party of two!). No one told us about that, no one pointed it out when we got the check, and it's definitely nothing other restaurants do in this area. This felt a bit weird. Hence the 3 stars.
Hidden treasure. Great food.

A romantic, upscale Italian restaurant in the heart of downtown Gainesville. A little pricey, but has large portions and really high quality food. Make sure to ask about parking, as it is a little confusing as to where you can and can't park.

Excellent food! Great pricing! The servers were very attentive and courteous. In fact, I caught our server watching us from across the room, just in case he saw anything we needed. The owner came by and checked to make sure everything was as great as it was.  Our first visit guarantees we will be back each time we go to Gainesville!
Fantastic food
Food was great portions were very large.  Owner came around and greeted every table.  Also plays a mean “happy Birthday “ on the sax.  Definitely a redo next time in Gainesville.
Try the lobster ravioli.
just alright.
The service was excellent and the food excellent. Pleasant atmosphere. I would recommend this place to anyone.
We go every year when in Gainesville for the NHRA Drag Races. Never Disappointed. Andy and his staff are good people.
Beautiful place

I went there with a group of nine people. Service was slow, food was ok at best and I found out that waiters can put their own tip (20% in this case) on the final price for serving a party that large… kinda defeats the purpose of tipping in the first place doesn’t it? Which, now that I think about it, might explain the slow service.  I’m giving it 2 out of 5 just because the restaurant looked good.
Great spot. Great cuisine!! The lunch specials are off the chain!!!
Best italian restaurant in town! I LOVE IT!

The food is superbly prepared with attention to taste and presentation. The service is excellent as well.  The owner/chef came out of the kitchen to play "Happy Birthday" on his sax to our 10 year old grandson.  It was a delightful evening.
The food in this restaurant is amazing! The atmosphere was welcoming! I would definitely recommend this for anyone who wants to take their significant other out for dinner!
The service isn't usually the best, but the food makes up for it. One of my go to's for Italian.

The food was fresh season just a little more garlic then I like that was everything had garlic cooked into it but overall a good meal. The staff was gracious and great we did our nephew 13th birthday dinner there.
Best eggplant parmesan I've ever had.
Friendly staff with a fresh, clean decor
Fine dining Italian, homemade pasta!
Good service, good food. Not exactly cheap but fair for the quality. I would go again
Very nice for a date, intimate, excellent food, wait staff perfect balance of available and unobtrusive
Best Salmon Ive ever had
Wonderful food. One of the only real chefs in Gainesville
Always great service
Went here for the first time recently and was pleasantly surprised. Food wasn't out of this world good but was pretty good for Italian food in Florida
I haven't been here in awhile, but I remember really liking this place. Food was good and prices reasonable.
This restaurant has a great staff and good tasting food.

My new favorite. I grew up going to the best Italian restaurants in New Jersey and this place is right up there with them. I’m so glad I found it. My daughter goes to school here now at UF so I am sure to come here every time I’m in town. I have the veal Sorrentino last night and it was amazing. Last time I had a different veal dish and it was also amazing. Their sauces are bursting with flavor. Even their bread inside pasta dishes or flavor bombs. The bread is crispy with rosemary and salt.  If you haven’t gone here yet you have to try it out. You will not regret it. I love this place- I even came here alone last night because my wife was too tired to go
Awesome!!!  The grouper was perfectly cooked.

Absolutely delicious. Small, only one waitress on duty for the entire lunch service. She turned away a few parties, and people got a bit salty about the wait time as she served all tables by herself.  However, the wait was worth it. Homemade pasta and delicious bread. I would definitely come back here again, and am only sad for the tables that didn't make the cut!

Cozy Italian classic with warm service and great food.  Located downtown in the square across from the Hippodrome Theater.  They serve an awesome lasagna and are willing to customize any plate to satisfy diet or taste.  Yum!

Decent Italian fare, but the real charm of Amelia's restaurant lies in the familial atmosphere. With a personable, and proud Chef-Owner who is happy to engage with and get feedback from customers, this restaurant reminds of eating in your family kitchen! Chicken Marsala was delicious, and the Bruschetta is a visual as well as delectable treat.
Very good food, large portions and some locally sourced ingredients.  Service was efficient, but the room a bit dated.  Could use a more robust wine selection.
Excellent meal and service!
Wonderful food, service, menu, atmosphere. Personal appearance from chef topped it off.
Very quaint. So friendly that the owner came by to check how the experience was. Perfect restaurant!!!
Great italian food and a super owner. Will defintely go back!
Good food, good service.
Andy the owner really cares about his business and it shows he also contributes to local events and the food is outstanding. If you are looking for great Italian cuisine look no further.
Friendly staff, wonderful food!
Best Italian food in Gainesville.  Chef Andy always delivers!

My wife and I dined here for our anniversary and it was way more than expected. Phenomenal service, and wonderful cozy environment. The owner/head chef is very courteous and welcoming. I had the surf and turf with the New York strip and it was the best thing I have ever tasted. My wife's food was amazing as well. I will definitely return and recommend to friends.

Meh.! This place was super meh. Not impressed at all and do not get all of the good reviews. Ordered seared portobellos. Literally sliced mushrooms on a plate with some spinach. Lobster ravioli was heavily coated in a meh sauce. Not a fan.
The food is amazing. The service is phenomenal. I don't have one negative thing to say about this place.
Very nice owner and staff. I was pleasantly surprised with the quality of the meal. Will return.

Great food, soo freakin good!!!! My fiancé doesn't eat very cultured foods, with that being said he enjoyed his surf n turf with smashed potatoes. The service was great and very diligent. I could be making tgis a regular date night place.
Great true Italian fare!  The atmosphere is awesome too!
The best Italian food in Gainesville.
Stumbled upon this place. Excellent, authentic Italian food. We were floored at the service, and the excellent quality of food!
Donald, the waiter, was very courteous and attentive. The environment and atmosphere was really nice and smooth. Great staff! The food was excellent and flavorful. Will come back for sure.

Great lunch special, the chef and service were fantastic. It is a little on the pricy side for lunch everyday but I could see myself there for lunch once a week or so. It was worth the money but if you're on a student budget just know what you're getting.
Really great food and service but it seems you pay more for the experience then the food based on what I got and how much I paid for it

We went for a special occasion but will definitely be returning more often. Very pleasant ambiance and all of us had excellent food, drink, and dessert. The chef and owner came out and said hello to everyone and even played happy birthday on the sax to one of the patrons.

I'm glad that we did not run into the non-reservation issue like others did. The salads were pretty awful. Super acidic dressing with no cheese or anything to counterbalance it. The wait time was close to an hour before we got our food. While my meal was delicious (Lobster Ravioli), it was only slightly better than chain Italian restaurants​ such as Olive Garden or Carrabba's. My friend ordered some sort of lasagna and was extremely dissatisfied with it. My experience wasn't​ bad, but I don't think I'll be returning as there are tons of other Italian options that are at a much more affordable cost and have better overall service.
The atmosphere is really nice and the food and prices are good.

We really enjoy everything about this cosy, delicious italian bistro. The owner /chef has it all, great skills and abilities and wonderful warm personality. It shows in the very tasty food, easy going experienced server staff and warm atmosphere.
Friendly staff and good food.

I am quite unhappy and taken aback by my recent experience at Amelia's. I've been here before and the food was absolutely delicious, so I was excited to take my friend here when she came to town. It was about 6:45 on a Thursday night and the restaurant was not too busy when we got there--we were hoping for outside seating since it was such a beautiful day out (there was no one outside at all). Well, we waited for 5 minutes before anyone came to the front, which was fine. However, we were met by a man who appeared to be a chef that asked us brashly "do you two have reservations?" I said no, because it's a Thursday night, not their typical busy Friday or Saturday, to which he responded with (in a very rude and annoyed tone): "well we only do reservations now, you'll have to come back at 8," and he walked away before I could even say anything. I even checked the website to see if it said reservations only, but it doesn't. I don't appreciate the fact that my friend and I appeared to be judged by him since we're 20-something year old college students. I will not be returning to this restaurant due to the treatment I received.

I have never talked about how good a plate of food was as much as I keep telling all my friends how amazing the lasagna tasted!! My boyfriend was willing to try something other than chicken parm at an Italian restaurant, for once. WE ABSOLUTELY MELTED WITH EVERY BITE!! It was funny we were kinda disappointed at the size of the lasagna piece but that completely went out the window when we had our first bite.  Both times I've gone have been for friends' birthday celebrations. They were not disappointed! For birthdays, the chef comes out with his saxophone and serenades the birthday person!! He also goes out of his way to ask how everything tasted. The chocolate cake we had for the birthday girl was pretty yummy too!  The restaurant is located in a cute little area of downtown Gainesville. It feels homey!  p.s. Can't wait to go back for more lasagna!
This is some of the best food Gainesville has to offer. If you really know and love Italian food Amelia's is a must.
I celebrated a big birthday last week at Bouley, and couldn't have chosen a better place!  Many Thanks!!!

The best Italian restaurant in Gainesville. The food is amazing but the ambiance and the staff make it even better. The owner/main chef always comes out and checks how the night is going. If you celebrate a event here you get a complimentary glass of champagne. Perfect experience every time! Thanks Andy!
The red sauce is so fresh. The food and service was excellent.
Excellent food. Great service. And an owner that truly cares about quality.

Let me start off by saying I am EXTREMELY happy I found this place 4 years ago. My friends and I came here for my birthday and it is by far my favorite place in Gainesville! I could eat here everyday if I could. Andy and the staff are the greatest and the service is impeccable. PLEASE try the Crostini for an appetizer, OMG will be the words that actually come out of your mouth when you try it! They bring a selection of hot bread to the table, not just one kind, usually 3 different kinds which are all very yummy and warm. The Surf and Turf, I can't even begin to tell you how amazing it is. Andy makes this most delicious blue cheese sauce to go with your perfect cooked steak, potatoes and shrimp. WOW. The Salmon Almondine, when its on the menu, you can not pass up on trying it. The salmon is cooked to perfection served over a bed of spinach, garlic grapes with this savory white sauce over it all. Just writing this review is making me hungry. They also have an amazing selection of wines to choose from and their dessert menu will not disappoint you! Make sure to try them out when you have the chance! Love you guys at Amelia's!!
Waitress was extremely rude. Inconsiderate and aggressive, food overpriced and nothing special.
The food is great.  I have eat here at least once a week. The service is good and fast so it's great for lunch.
Never a bad meal. Always excellent customer service,  like family.

No bueno. Terrible services , food is a 3 out of 10, overpriced - over rated. Maybe it was becuase i have an accent that the waiter didn't feel like explaining us the menu or gretting us at all.  Jesus im disgusted by this restaurant. Maybe my hopes were to high. But no the food here is not delicious or exquisite. Don't let the other comments convince you. This is coming from an international chef. Your welcome.
We had an excellent experience. The service, food and setting was great. Would definitely recommend.
Been coming here for years. The food and the service are always great. Love their pasta dishes.

I call to place a pickup order and some guy picks up the phone and tells me "absolutelly not, we don't do pick up orders on a busy Friday". Why all that unnecessary verbiage when a simple "no" in a nice tone would suffice? I'm taking my take out and dine-in business elsewhere, for all fridays and for less busy days too.
Absolutely delicious food, best Italian restaurant in Gainesville!!! The Crostini NY is to die for! Very friendly owner, staff & atmosphere! Our go to spot from now on, thanks! D&L Performance
Delicious food.   The serve was fast and polite.  The chef walked around as we ate and checked on each diner.

Food was fantastic, wait staff was amazing and the restaurant is beautiful. Everything we ordered was delicious. It was an amazing experience all around and I definitely want to go back to try out the rest of the menu because everything else I didn't get to try sounded delicious.

Maybe I expected too much. There were so many good reviews on this place but my experience was 1 star at best. Blan appetizer, house salad had 1 cucumber slice 1 carrot slice and one canned mushroom cap. Wife's entree was unedible and the pasta that came with mine was comparable to Fazoli's. Will not be returning :(

I went for my birthday June 3rd, staff was amazing, very attentive to every need. We started of with appetizers, I had the capprese and my husband had the calamari. We paired that with Moscato recommended by our server. For the main course,  I had the lasagna which was an enormous portion (made really tasty leftovers), the sauce was mild not too acidic. My husband had the surf and turf, again enormous portions. Had to box that yummy goodness up to make room for desserts. I choose the chocolate mouse cake and my husband had the flan...both very delectable. I would highly recommend this establishment to anybody who prefers real Italian food, great service and good prices. I don't recommend bringing the kids, definitely nice and cozy for a romantic dinner.

Casual atmosphere and great friendly service. The special appetizers were amazing and plentiful. The fresh bread and entrees were great. You can taste the quality and freshness. Highly recommended. It made for a great date night.
The Lunch Bunch had a very enjoyable lunch today.  Lunch specials are a very good deal. Good choice for lunch downtown Gainesville.
The pesto pasta was great, but the almond custard was absolutely amazing. The atmosphere was pleasant.
LOVED Amelia's so much I went back for my birthday dinner. The pasta is out of this world. You can taste the quality. 5 stars
We are huge fans of this place. Chef Andy rocks and always helps us get the best stuff for our 4 year old daughter. Never had a dud of a meal here.

The food was delicious and the service overall amicable. The only complaint I have that as my friend walked in for our reservation, the waitress tried to send her to a different restaurant. When she said she was at the right place, the waitress then proceeded to ask if she was doing take-out, and my friend was very embarrassed that this waitress gave her such a hard time. She was dressed appropriately and has been to the restaurant before, and I must say I was disappointed in how this waitress treated her.

Because of it's awesome location adjacent the Hippodrome Theater in downtown Gainesville, I tried Amelia's once, and I have been a happy, satisfied and loyal patron ever since!  The food is fine dining and nothing you would ever find at lower end restaurants, but it is surprisingly affordable.  Great way to get exposed to fantastic cuisine.  Their wine selection is excellent.  It is a great date spot and I always refer business associated who are in from out to town - don't miss your chance to enjoy a fantastic meal in a great environment.  Chef Andy is THE BEST!

My wife and I celebrated an early Valentines day by having dinner at Amelia's.  We started with a spinach and artichoke dip that was great.  My wife had the Lobster Ravioli which was excellent and I had the Grouper special that was wonderful.  We highly recommend Amelia's for a fine Italian meal!

Owner is Chief.  After 55 minutes we did not have any food.  Complained to hostess and waiter and finally got our salads delivered. Problem is chief/owner is in kitchen and no one running front of house to solve problems.  Ordered a $60 bottle of red wine and it was delivered at room temp, about 80 degrees.  Had to cool wine to drink which took 15 minutes.  They had red wines up to a $100 but don't keep any reds at proper temp. Nice place and good food but no one at home in the front of the house.
Pricey, but good decor and food.

Fancy being fancy? Great atmosphere, amazing calamari and the gnocchi is to die for! I haven't had such an amazing gnocchi dish since I was in California. Delightful staff and the head chef is a Gator Grad, props to him for coming out and saying hello. Amazing dinner, we had a party of 8 and I don't think anyone had complaints about their dish. The bread is also baked fresh and it's always a different type.
